<div xmlns="http://www.tei-c.org/ns/1.0" xml:id="trans-illegiblecharunknown" xml:lang="en">
    <head>Illegible Characters, Quantity Unknown</head>
    <p><!--gloss--></p>
    <p><specList>
        <specDesc key="gap"/>
    </specList>
        <!--<listRef>
            <ptr target="a"/>
            </listRef>--></p> 
    
    <p>Where vestiges of characters remain, but they cannot be recognised and their quantity is
        unknown, they should be placed in a <gi>gap</gi> and given a <att>reason</att>
        with a value of "illegible" and an <att>extent</att> with a value of "unknown".</p>
    
    <cit>
        <quote>[- - -]</quote>
        <bibl corresp="#panciera"> <!-- VIII.3 is a normal gap (characters lost, extent unknown) - there is no Panciera section corresponding exactly to 'Illegible Characters, Quantity Unknown' but I think this would be rendered the same way -->
            <biblScope>VIII.3</biblScope>
        </bibl>
        <bibl corresp="#ddbdp"/>
        <!-- etc. -->
    </cit>
    
    <egXML xmlns="http://www.tei-c.org/ns/Examples" corresp="#panciera">
        <gap reason="illegible" extent="unknown" unit="character"/>
    </egXML>
    
    <egXML xmlns="http://www.tei-c.org/ns/Examples" rend="london" corresp="http://inslib.kcl.ac.uk/irt2009/IRT045.html">
        <gap reason="illegible" extent="unknown" unit="character"/>
    </egXML>
    
    <egXML xmlns="http://www.tei-c.org/ns/Examples" rend="ddbdp" corresp="http://papyri.info/ddbdp/bgu;10;1926">
        <gap reason="illegible" extent="unknown" unit="character"/>
    </egXML>
    
    <divGen type="seealso"/>
    
